1463
01:12:39,969 --> 01:12:41,470
Yes! Explain that.

1464
01:12:41,570 --> 01:12:43,539
We used to play this game, all right?

1465
01:12:43,640 --> 01:12:45,542
Buddy and I, when we
were young, he would...

1466
01:12:45,641 --> 01:12:48,278
It was called the
Ghost and the Damsel.

1467
01:12:48,377 --> 01:12:50,345
And he would blindfold me.

1468
01:12:50,445 --> 01:12:52,916
Then he'd put a sheet
above himself...

1469
01:12:53,015 --> 01:12:55,051
and then I would have
to search about...

1470
01:12:55,150 --> 01:12:57,186
and capture the rapture,
if you know what I mean.

1471
01:12:57,287 --> 01:12:58,854
Mama!

1472
01:12:58,954 --> 01:13:00,457
I am sorry, Conner.

1473
01:13:00,556 --> 01:13:02,826
- That's just nasty.
- Sorry, Son.

1474
01:13:02,926 --> 01:13:05,060
- But I like it.
- I know.

1475
01:13:05,161 --> 01:13:07,529
It can be fun. It can be.

1476
01:13:07,630 --> 01:13:10,466
That is so inappropriate.

1477
01:13:10,567 --> 01:13:14,136
You two need to learn how to
respect my daughter's house.

1478
01:13:15,003 --> 01:13:17,774
- Eileen, you might wanna let that go.
- No.

1479
01:13:17,873 --> 01:13:19,943
They come in here taking
advantage of her...

1480
01:13:20,042 --> 01:13:23,445
eating her food, and they're
acting like they own the place.

1481
01:13:23,546 --> 01:13:25,715
- I don't like it.
- You need to let that go.

1482
01:13:25,814 --> 01:13:28,417
Well, I don't like...

1483
01:13:28,518 --> 01:13:30,686
- Mama...
- that you...

1484
01:13:30,787 --> 01:13:32,255
Mama, sit down.

1485
01:13:32,354 --> 01:13:34,890
You cut down my family's memory tree.

1486
01:13:34,990 --> 01:13:36,960
That's what I don't like.

1487
01:13:37,060 --> 01:13:38,560
Excuse me?

1488
01:13:38,661 --> 01:13:41,663
I can deal with a lot of things.
They know it.

1489
01:13:41,764 --> 01:13:44,199
But this is downright wrong...

1490
01:13:44,300 --> 01:13:47,243
and now I am getting very upset!

1491
01:13:48,003 --> 01:13:51,240
Why would you plant his memory
tree on my daughter's land...

1492
01:13:51,341 --> 01:13:53,309
and how was I supposed to know that?

1493
01:13:53,408 --> 01:13:55,377
Oh, I don't know.

1494
01:13:55,478 --> 01:13:58,480
Maybe because it had a
yellow ribbon around it?

1495
01:13:58,581 --> 01:14:00,182
That doesn't mean anything.

1496
01:14:00,283 --> 01:14:03,720
In most countries, in most places,
to sane-thinking people...

1497
01:14:03,819 --> 01:14:06,488
a yellow ribbon means something.

1498
01:14:06,588 --> 01:14:10,560
Now you just calm down, missy. Okay?

1499
01:14:10,659 --> 01:14:14,663
Now, Lacey, are you gonna
let her talk to me like this?

1500
01:14:14,764 --> 01:14:16,666
- Mama, calm down.
- Put your finger down...

1501
01:14:16,765 --> 01:14:19,005
or I will cut it off and deep-fry it!

1502
01:14:20,302 --> 01:14:22,838
You need to leave my
daughter's house.

1503
01:14:22,939 --> 01:14:24,806
- Mama, stop it! Stop!
- No!

1504
01:14:24,907 --> 01:14:26,775
Eileen, you need to
stop right now, honey.

1505
01:14:26,876 --> 01:14:29,712
What are they doing here anyway?
Tomorrow is Christmas!

1506
01:14:29,811 --> 01:14:31,346
They are not your family!

1507
01:14:31,447 --> 01:14:33,682
- Let's get out of here.
- No, hold up.

1508
01:14:33,783 --> 01:14:36,085
Come on back here.
Ain't nobody going nowhere.

1509
01:14:36,185 --> 01:14:38,820
- Now, Madea...
- Ain't nobody goin' no damn where.

1510
01:14:38,921 --> 01:14:40,890
Madea, whose side are you on?

1511
01:14:40,989 --> 01:14:43,359
- Let 'em leave.
- No, I'm on the side of right.

1512
01:14:43,458 --> 01:14:45,561
- That's the side I'm on. Lacey?
- Yes.

1513
01:14:45,662 --> 01:14:48,664
- Tell your mama.
- What? Tell me what?

1514
01:14:48,765 --> 01:14:52,005
Spit it out before I punch you,
put your teeth down your throat!

1515
01:14:54,537 --> 01:14:57,480
Mama... Conner and I are married.

1516
01:15:01,577 --> 01:15:03,987
- Catch her.
- Get the defibrillator.

1517
01:15:09,185 --> 01:15:11,730
Lacey. Your father.

1518
01:15:12,689 --> 01:15:15,692
I know, Mama. I know he was
murdered by a white man, but...

1519
01:15:15,792 --> 01:15:17,292
- What happened?
- What?

1520
01:15:17,393 --> 01:15:20,662
My father was killed by a
white man on Christmas Eve...

1521
01:15:20,762 --> 01:15:22,564
trying to protect my mother's honor.

1522
01:15:22,664 --> 01:15:24,667
- That's awful.
- Good Lord.

1523
01:15:24,766 --> 01:15:27,770
- Who told you that?
- Mama.

1524
01:15:27,869 --> 01:15:31,039
Eileen, you oughta be ashamed...
Child, that's some straight-up bull...

1525
01:15:31,140 --> 01:15:32,547
Madea!

1526
01:15:33,141 --> 01:15:35,721
Your daddy wasn't
killed by no white man.

1527
01:15:36,311 --> 01:15:38,680
He left your mama for a white
woman when you was two...

1528
01:15:38,780 --> 01:15:41,117
and your mama has been bitter
with white people ever since.

1529
01:15:41,216 --> 01:15:42,685
- What?
- Yes, years ago.

1530
01:15:42,784 --> 01:15:47,090
Ran off and joined the circus.
And now they on Glee,

1531
01:15:47,189 --> 01:15:48,658
Good show.

1532
01:15:48,757 --> 01:15:51,600
Glee? Mama, is this true?

1533
01:15:52,528 --> 01:15:54,197
Mama!

1534
01:15:54,296 --> 01:15:59,935
Lacey, I am so disappointed in you.

1535
01:16:00,036 --> 01:16:02,412
Look at her trying to
turn it around on you.

1536
01:16:03,405 --> 01:16:04,984
Girl, please.

1537
01:16:09,746 --> 01:16:11,552
You're disappointed in me?

1538
01:16:12,314 --> 01:16:14,550
Well, that went well.

1539
01:16:14,649 --> 01:16:16,957
At least she didn't have
another heart attack.

1540
01:16:18,587 --> 01:16:20,657
- Another one?
- Yeah, Madea.

1541
01:16:20,756 --> 01:16:23,659
Didn't you know that my mother
had a heart attack last year?

1542
01:16:23,760 --> 01:16:25,895
Your mama lied to you. She had gas.

1543
01:16:25,994 --> 01:16:28,831
Got to the doctor, she was clutching
her heart and the pearls.

1544
01:16:28,930 --> 01:16:31,234
Got there, doctor say it's gas.

1545
01:16:31,333 --> 01:16:34,837
- Wait, what?
- They put one of them rods up there.

1546
01:16:34,936 --> 01:16:37,806
Came flowing out like the River Jordan
and that was it. It was all over.

1547
01:16:37,907 --> 01:16:39,375
I had that once too.

1548
01:16:39,475 --> 01:16:41,978
Put it in there, come out sounding
like brakes coming out of...

1549
01:16:42,078 --> 01:16:44,488
The air pressure coming
out of one of them big rigs.

1550
01:16:45,515 --> 01:16:47,750
There it is. Then they tell
her she had heartburn.

1551
01:16:47,850 --> 01:16:50,586
- She didn't have no heart attack.
